    public abstract class FileOrCLIMonitor
extends Monitor
    Base class for a Monitor that prints to the standard output stream (console) and/or a file.

      • write

        protected void write(Observable observed,
         java.lang.Object event,
         java.lang.Object state,
         java.lang.CharSequence s)
        Write the given CharSequence as a new line (for example a String) to the console and/or file according to the settings.
        Parameters:
        observed - The subject (the object being observed). Provided for context, may be ignored.
        event - An object indicating the type of change or event, this is usually an defined by the Subject. If null is given then the Observer(s) will be passed Observable.Event.Unspecified. Provided for context, may be ignored.
        state - An arbitrary object typically describing the current state of the Observable or information about the event. Provided for context, may be ignored.
        s - The character sequence to write.
        See Also:
        Observer.eventOccurred(Observable, Object, Object)
